  "prompt": "How do I start an airport shuttle business?",
  "response": "To start an airport shuttle business, follow these steps:\n\n1. Research and Planning\n- Study local market demand\n- Create a comprehensive business plan\n- Determine startup costs and potential revenue\n- Identify target customer segments\n\n2. Legal Requirements\n- Register your business\n- Obtain necessary business licenses\n- Get commercial insurance\n- Acquire required transportation permits\n- Meet state and local transportation regulations\n\n3. Vehicle Acquisition\n- Purchase or lease appropriate shuttle vehicles\n- Choose vehicles with good fuel efficiency\n- Consider wheelchair-accessible options\n- Ensure vehicles meet safety standards\n\n4. Infrastructure Setup\n- Develop booking and reservation system\n- Create a website and online booking platform\n- Set up customer service phone line\n- Establish pricing structure\n\n5. Marketing\n- Create a professional brand\n- Develop marketing materials\n- Build online presence\n- Network with hotels, travel agencies, and airports\n- Use digital advertising and social media\n\n6. Operational Considerations\n- Hire reliable drivers\n- Conduct background checks\n- Provide driver training\n- Implement scheduling and dispatch systems\n- Establish maintenance protocols for vehicles\n\n7. Financial Management\n- Open a business bank account\n- Track expenses and revenue\n- Set competitive pricing\n- Consider financing options if needed\n\n8. Continuous Improvement\n- Gather customer feedback\n- Monitor industry trends\n- Adapt services as needed",
